The paper deals with algorithms for listing patterns in graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorics. The use of dynamic data structures and lower bounds on the number of patterns suggests a focus on algorithm design and analysis, which is typically associated with the cs.DS and cs.DM sub-categories. The problem of listing patterns in graphs is also related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the potential applications of graph pattern mining in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) further support this list of likely sub-categories.
